Let's pick a language of choice as Java

> Strategy 0 -  Rule out the comments

Original code space : 
In the majority of the situations, there will not be useful information
present in the comment blocks or headers, since the models are smart enough
to understand the context directly from the actual code.

Mapping to Compressed space : 
The engine scrapes out all the comment blocks and generates the compressed space. 
More importantly, it carries the mapping of this compressed space to the original 
code space.

Model response : 
This compressed code space block is now sent as context to the model and the model 
returns modifications on top of the compressed space itself. 

Unmapping to original space: 
Using the mapping created earlier, we will unwrap and generate the original code blocks 
from this compressed code block.


> Strategy 1 - Ask type, compact blocks

If it is a plain ask query, there are lot of scenarios where we can write code in 
a much compacter way and get the answer queried, rather than sending as is, either 
compacting within the same language or a different language.